<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000023#     1#         2705#">Va. Code Ann. § 23.1-2705</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_23.1-2705"/><heading><desig>§ 23.1-2705.</desig><title>(Effective October 1, 2016) Gifts, grants, devises, and bequests; governmental aid</title></heading><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_a"/><heading><desig>A.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> The board may take, hold, receive, and enjoy any gift, grant, devise, or bequest to the board or to or for the benefit of the University. Any such gift, grant, devise, or bequest shall be used for the purposes designated by the donor, or if no purposes are so designated, for the general purposes of the board.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_b"/><heading><desig>B.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> The University shall receive the governmental aid designated in §§ 23.1-2638 and 23.1-2639.</p></bodyText></level><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p>Code 1919, § 957, <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 23-170"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 23 -170">§ 23-170<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#123#000023#       170#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>; 1930, p. 769; 1964, c. 70; 1979, c. 147; <citation normalizedCite="2016 VA CH 588"><content><span normalizedCite="2016 Va. Ch. 588">2016, c. 588<locator><locatorKey><keyName na